  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\nPart of #930 \r\n\r\n- The [helper functions in beacon_chain](https://github.com/ethereum/beacon_chain/blob/master/beacon_chain/state/helpers.py) are all pure functions with a `config: Dict[string, Any]` parameter. \r\n- Some helpers functions are like ~90% similar to [the spec](https://notes.ethereum.org/s/Syj3QZSxm#Helper-functions) as a reference implementation. But to fit Py-EVM paradigm, we may have to refactor a lot.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\nIt may take multiple steps:\r\n1. Move all pure functions to `eth/beacon/helpers.py` - I have a commit here: https://github.com/hwwhww/py-evm/commit/5724a7a30ce56979382c7ea07e29e08fcaf21254 \r\n2. Introduce `eth.beacon.db.chain.BeaconChainDB`\r\n3. Introduce `eth.beacon.state_machines.base.BaseStateMachine(Configurable)`\r\n4. Introduce `eth.beacon.chains.chain.BeaconChain`\r\n4. Tear down helpers: move some of them to `eth.beacon.state_machine.base.BaseStateMachine` or being static functions / properties in `eth.beacon.types.*` classes.\r\n\r\ncc @djrtwo @pipermerriam ",
